(4, 'What is an abstract class?', 'Has no methods at all', 'Cannot be instantiated directly', 'Has only static methods', 'Is always final', 'B'),
(4, 'Which SOLID principle says a class should have one reason to change?', 'Open/Closed Principle', 'Single Responsibility Principle', 'Liskov Substitution', 'Dependency Inversion', 'B'),
(4, 'What is a constructor?', 'A method that destroys objects', 'A special method called when an object is created', 'A static method', 'A void method', 'B'),
(4, 'What does the super keyword refer to in Java?', 'Current class', 'Parent class', 'Child class', 'Interface', 'B'),
