(4, 'What is the Decorator pattern?', 'Subclassing behavior', 'Adds responsibilities to objects dynamically', 'Creates object factories', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the difference between composition and inheritance?', 'No difference', 'Composition uses HAS-A, inheritance uses IS-A', 'Inheritance uses HAS-A', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Open/Closed Principle?', 'Open for deletion, closed for addition', 'Open for extension, closed for modification', 'Open source code principle', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Liskov Substitution Principle?', 'Child class can replace parent without errors', 'Parent class replaces child', 'Methods must be static', 'None', 'A'),
(4, 'What is dependency injection?', 'Creating objects inside class', 'Providing dependencies from outside the class', 'Using static methods', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Interface Segregation Principle?', 'Use as few interfaces as possible', 'No client should be forced to implement unused methods', 'Interfaces must be abstract', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Dependency Inversion Principle?', 'Depend on concrete classes', 'Depend on abstractions, not concretions', 'Avoid interfaces', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Strategy design pattern?', 'Creates one strategy', 'Defines a family of algorithms, encapsulate each, make interchangeable', 'Observes state changes', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Template Method pattern?', 'Creates templates for objects', 'Defines algorithm skeleton, subclasses fill in details', 'Provides object creation', 'None', 'B'),
