(4, 'What is the Facade pattern?', 'Creates complex objects', 'Provides simplified interface to complex subsystem', 'Adds responsibilities', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Adapter pattern?', 'Creates new objects', 'Converts interface of one class to another expected by client', 'Observes changes', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the difference between interface and abstract class?', 'Interface can have method implementations', 'Interface supports multiple inheritance, abstract class does not', 'Abstract class is faster', 'No difference', 'B'),
(4, 'What is encapsulation?', 'Hiding implementation inside a class using access modifiers', 'Extending functionality', 'Creating multiple forms', 'None', 'A'),
(4, 'What is abstraction in OOP?', 'Showing all details', 'Hiding complexity and showing only essential features', 'Same as encapsulation', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is method overriding?', 'Same class, different method', 'Child class provides specific implementation of parent method', 'Static method replacement', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is a design pattern?', 'A fixed algorithm', 'A reusable solution to commonly occurring problem', 'A programming language feature', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Proxy pattern?', 'Creates objects directly', 'Provides placeholder/surrogate for another object', 'Simplifies interface', 'None', 'B'),
(4, 'What is the Command pattern?', 'Executes commands sequentially', 'Encapsulates a request as an object', 'Creates command-line tools', 'None', 'B'),
