(12, 'What does the BETWEEN operator do?', 'Matches values outside a range', 'Selects values within a given range (inclusive)', 'Groups table columns', 'None of these', 'B'),
(12, 'How do you check for NULL values in SQL?', 'column = NULL', 'column IS NULL', 'column IS NOT EMPTY', 'column = ""', 'B'),
(12, 'What is a View in SQL?', 'A database table structure', 'A virtual table based on the result-set of an SQL statement', 'An index backup', 'None of these', 'B'),
