(13, 'How should you typically answer: "Tell me about yourself"?', 'List your personal hobbies and family background', 'Briefly highlight educational background, key achievements, and relevant project experience', 'Read your entire resume line-by-line', 'Describe your salary expectations', 'B'),
(13, 'What does the STAR method stand for in behavioral interviews?', 'Situation, Task, Action, Result', 'Schedule, Task, Agreement, Review', 'Status, Target, Answer, Resolution', 'None of these', 'A'),
(13, 'How should you handle answering: "What are your weaknesses"?', 'Say: "I have no weaknesses, I am perfect"', 'Share a real professional weakness you identified and show steps you took to improve it', 'Describe a weakness that makes you look bad in every way', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is the best way to prepare for a company interview?', 'Research the company background, mission, projects, and study core technical subjects', 'Show up without any preparation to look natural', 'Study only salary structures', 'None of these', 'A'),
(13, 'How should you describe your final year project during an interview?', 'Say it was simple and copy-pasted', 'Explain the project goal, your role, technical stack used, challenges faced, and results achieved', 'Just read the project title', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What should you do if you do not know the answer to a technical question?', 'Guess randomly and try to bluff the interviewer', 'Be honest, state your current understanding, and explain how you would search for the solution', 'Stay silent and wait for the next question', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you behave when asked situational question: "How do you handle conflict in a team"?', 'Say you avoid working in teams', 'Describe a professional framework for listening, discussing, finding a compromise, and focusing on goal', 'Blame others for conflicts', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is a good question to ask the interviewer at the end?', 'What is the salary and when do I get leaves?', 'What does a typical day look like in this role, and what are the main challenges?', 'I have no questions', 'How did I perform?', 'B'),
(13, 'What should your self-introduction focus on for a technical role?', 'Your family history', 'Your technical skills, frameworks learned, coding practice, and engineering projects', 'Your favorite movies and books', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you show "Strengths" in an interview?', 'State you are a hard worker without examples', 'Provide specific instances where your strengths (e.g. fast learning, problem solving) resolved a problem', 'Describe strengths unrelated to work', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is the purpose of behavioral interview questions?', 'To check your writing skills', 'To evaluate past behavior as a predictor of future performance in similar scenarios', 'To test your math skills', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you structure your resume sections?', 'Random order', 'Contact, Objective/Summary, Education, Technical Skills, Projects, Achievements, Experience', 'Hobbies first, education last', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is the ideal length of a college placement resume?', '1 page', '3 to 4 pages', '5 pages', 'As long as possible', 'A'),
(13, 'How should you handle the question: "Why do you want to join our company"?', 'Say you want a job because you need money', 'Align your career goals with the company''s mission, culture, products, and growth opportunities', 'Say you chose it randomly', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What does eye contact show in an interview?', 'Aggression', 'Confidence, engagement, and sincerity', 'Disinterest', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is the purpose of mock interviews during placement prep?', 'A formal evaluation that gets recorded in university file', 'To practice communication, reduce interview anxiety, and refine answering frameworks', 'To pass time', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you follow up after an interview?', 'Call the interviewer repeatedly every hour', 'Send a polite thank-you email within 24 hours highlighting your interest in the role', 'Do nothing at all', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What does a clean resume formatting reflect to the recruiter?', 'Lack of content', 'Attention to detail, professionalism, and organization skills', 'That it was designed by someone else', 'None of these', 'B'),
