(13, 'How should you answer the question: "How do you prioritize multiple tasks under tight deadlines"?', 'Work on whatever is easiest first', 'Explain a system of ranking by urgency vs importance, communicating delays early, and managing time blocks', 'Refuse to work on weekends', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is the role of body language in interviews?', 'Has zero impact', 'Highly impactful in conveying enthusiasm, engagement, and confidence', 'Only matters for HR roles', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you describe your extracurricular activities?', 'List every activity since childhood', 'Highlight leadership, teamwork, or organizational skills developed through key activities', 'Describe them briefly without detailing skills', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is the best way to showcase problem-solving skills?', 'State you are a good problem solver', 'Walk through a specific, challenging technical problem you solved, detailing the process and result', 'Say you don''t face problems', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you respond if asked about your expected salary as a fresher?', 'Demand a high number immediately', 'State you are open to industry standard guidelines for freshers, focusing first on learning opportunity', 'Say you don''t care about salary', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What should you do to prepare your environment for a virtual interview?', 'Choose a quiet room with clean background, test internet, microphone, and camera in advance', 'Set up in a noisy cafeteria to show multitasking', 'Use low light settings to hide background details', 'None of these', 'A'),
(13, 'What is the role of technical stack choice in resume projects?', 'Adding complex-sounding names to bypass filters', 'Demonstrating that you chose appropriate tools to solve the project''s specific requirements', 'Irrelevant to freshers', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you handle the question: "Are you willing to relocate"?', 'Say absolutely no immediately if unsure', 'State your preference clearly, but express willingness to relocate if it is a great career opportunity', 'Lie and say yes even if you won''t', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What does the term "thought process" mean during coding interviews?', 'Silent thinking', 'Explaining your design decisions, algorithm choices, and logic out loud while writing code', 'Writing multiple solutions simultaneously', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you handle a mistake you made during the interview?', 'Pretend it did not happen and ignore it', 'Politely acknowledge it, correct yourself, and maintain a positive attitude', 'Apologize repeatedly and lose focus', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What does standard resume summary outline?', 'Your family details', 'A 2-3 sentence overview of your key skills, education, and placement goals', 'Your salary expectations', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'Why is it important to customize your resume for different job descriptions?', 'Bypasses search filters by matching key skills and shows targeted interest', 'No importance, one resume fits all', 'Makes resume longer', 'None of these', 'A'),
(13, 'What is the role of projects section on a fresher''s resume?', 'Fills empty page space', 'Crucial in proving practical implementation of theoretical engineering concepts', 'Has no impact', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How should you answer: "Why should we hire you"?', 'Say: "Because I am the best candidate"', 'Summarize your matching skills, enthusiasm, and explain how you can add value to the team', 'Describe your financial needs', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What does maintaining high energy and enthusiasm show during an interview?', 'Desperation', 'Genuine interest in the role, company, and team success', 'Unprofessionalism', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'What is the impact of non-technical skills (soft skills) in placement interviews?', 'Zero impact, only coding matters', 'Highly important as they impact team collaboration, leadership potential, and client interactions', 'Only matters for managers', 'None of these', 'B'),
(13, 'How do you demonstrate continuous learning on a resume?', 'Listing courses you took years ago', 'Listing recent certifications, online bootcamps, or personal coding projects in new frameworks', 'Listing hobbies', 'None of these', 'B'),
